	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">I have phenomenally bad luck on pick-up group loot methods.<br />
<br />
This is not the result of poor ethics on my pick-up group companions.   It's just really poor luck.<br />
<br />
I have done about 30 adventures, and about half of them, we're NBG (need before greed) and the other half, we're roll for everything.<br />
<br />
Aside from augs, which I flat out refuse to roll for if they're not useful to me, I've seen 2 awesome cleric items come up, for my level.  One was a mask, the other was a set of vambraces.  Both would have been very nice upgrades to me, and in one case, I was the only person in the group who could use them.  Both occured in roll for everything groups, and I did not win the roll.<br />
<br />
I have seen countless nice items for my alts or my g/f's characters come up, and they always do so when I'm in NBG groups.<br />
<br />
All in all, I prefer NBG.  It tore my heart out to watch a monk walk away with the plate class arms I needed so bad, and a SK walk away with a +8 wisdom mask that he openly said 'would be for an alt he never played, but cool!'<br />
<br />
But, if you're rolling, you're rolling.  It may seem like dirty poker when you lose the roll to some guy who seems like he must be performing sexual favors for the RNG.  But them's the breaks.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><img src="/forums/images/sig_separator.gif" width="282" height="11" Alt="Hey! Watch where you point that thing!"><br>
<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">

