	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">I believe NBG should be the norm for drops and always insist on this when I have any say in the matter.  However, should an item drop which is considered gravy then I have no problem with someone rolling for an alt or for selling or for whatever they want to do with the item.  If the poll was written with strictly NBG rules in mind then only the characters being played in the group should be considered.  If that means the item defaults to the only person in the group who can and will use it then so be it.<br />
<br />
I will not stay long with a group that is not NBG.  Nor will I group twice with a player who insists on rolling for everything.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><img src="/forums/images/sig_separator.gif" width="282" height="11" Alt="Hey! Watch where you point that thing!"><br>
